  "prompt": "What is the best way to substitute celery seeds in a recipe?",
  "response": "If you need to substitute celery seeds in a recipe, there are several alternatives you can consider:\n\n1. **Celery Salt**: This is one of the closest substitutes. Keep in mind that it contains salt, so you may need to adjust the salt content in your recipe. Use about twice the amount of celery salt to replace celery seeds, then reduce other added salt accordingly.\n\n2. **Fresh Celery**: If you're able to dice it finely, fresh celery can replicate the flavor, although it will add moisture and texture. Use about 3-4 times the amount of fresh celery for the equivalent flavor.\n\n3. **Dill Seeds**: These can impart a somewhat similar earthy flavor. Use them in equal amounts as a substitute.\n\n4. **Caraway Seeds**: These seeds have a different flavor profile but some of the same earthy and slightly bitter notes. Use them sparingly, starting with a little less than what the recipe calls for in celery seeds, and adjust to taste.\n\n5. **Parsley or Lovage**: These herbs can provide some of the green, herbaceous notes that celery seeds offer. Use a bit more than the amount of celery seeds required as a rough equivalent.\n\nWhen substituting, keep in mind the flavor profile of your dish and how much of the celery seed is required, as it might be necessary to tweak other flavors to achieve the desired result.",
